	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64600963"><p>The dinner fork was invented in 18th century Germany. That's the one with four tines and a curve to it, suitable for both piercing and scooping food. They're very nice and you don't need to design your food around them like with chopsticks. Much better than the forks you are talking about with two long skinny prongs, or the one-prong forks invented in prehistory.</p></div>
	</div>

